# Approach
Idea is to delete an edge connecting a and b, and then find the minimum distance between a and b (without considering the deleted edge), this shortest path plus one is the size of the smallest loop having both nodes a and b. 
Repeat the same for each edge and return the the size of minimum loop.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(E^2)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

